# Directory Structure Rules

## Structure Compliance
### AI Management Files
- `.project_management/` - All AI collaboration files
- `.cursor/rules/` - Cursor IDE behavior rules
- `.old_temporary_files/` - Archived temporary files

### Django Project Structure  
- `apps/` - Django applications only
- `scripts/` - Utility scripts
- `html_analysis_tools/` - HTML processing utilities
- `tests/` - Test files
- `config/` - Configuration files

## Prohibited Actions
- Creating files outside defined structure
- Making temporary files in root directory
- Modifying production database without permission
- Renaming core Django files without approval

## Required Actions  
- Update `triad_project_architecture.org` when adding files
- Use naming conventions: `YYYY-MM-DD` for dates
- Generate cleanup reports in `.project_management/cleanup_reports/`
- Respect Django project structure

## File Locations
### Scripts and Utilities
- Scripts: `scripts/` directory
- Tests: `test_*.py` naming
- Analysis outputs: dated directories
- Logs: designated locations

### AI Files
- Conversation logs: `.project_management/conversation_logs/[model-name]/`
- Cleanup reports: `.project_management/cleanup_reports/`
- Next steps: `.project_management/next_steps/`

